  "prompt": "Can a killer whale eat a stingray?",
  "response": "Yes, killer whales (orcas) can eat stingrays. Killer whales are apex predators and have a diverse diet that can include fish, squid, seals, and even large marine mammals. Depending on their location and the specific pods, they may also prey on other marine animals such as stingrays. Their hunting techniques and ability to adapt to different types of prey allow them to include a variety of species in their diet.",
